A memorial service has been held where Dumisani Joxo took his last breath. Joxo was allegedly murdered by a 22-year-old law enforcement officer last weekend. eNCA's Ronald Masinda was also there. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The gunning down of a homeless man, allegedly by a City of Cape Town law enforcement officer, shows a disregard for the human rights of the homeless. This is the sentiment that’s echoed throughout Dumisani Joxo’s memorial service. His family, friends and several activists were in attendance. EXCLUSIVE | Murdered homeless man's girlfriend speaks Joxo was allegedly murdered by a law enforcement officer last weekend. And while the matter is still being investigated, there seem to be many unanswered questions. * eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports.